message.text:
#TamAnunsyo | As of today, September 16, 2025, the Far Eastern University has officially announced that both FEU Manila and Makati campuses will shift to synchronous classes on September 17, 2025, due to the 3-day transport strike by Manibela.

Students are encouraged to coordinate with their instructors for guidance on class activities for the day. The university is also encouraging students to check Canvas for the official FEU Protocol on Learning Modalities during the suspension of on-campus classes.

Further, take note that university offices, including the Main Library, Shared Hybrid Learning Spaces, and The Huddle, will remain open for onsite transactions and student use.

Stay updated through our TamAnunsyo. 

Source: Far Eastern University 

#TamaRiseTogether 
#FEUCSO90

#TamAnunsyo | As of today, September 16, 2025, the Far Eastern University has officially announced that both FEU Manila and Makati campuses will shift to synchronous classes on September 17, 2025, due to the 3-day transport strike by Manibela.

Students are encouraged to coordinate with their instructors for guidance on class activities for the day. The university is also encouraging students to check Canvas for the official FEU Protocol on Learning Modalities during the suspension of on-campus classes.

Further, take note that university offices, including the Main Library, Shared Hybrid Learning Spaces, and The Huddle, will remain open for onsite transactions and student use.

Stay updated through our TamAnunsyo. 

Source: Far Eastern University

#TamAnunsyo | As of today, September 16, 2025, the Far Eastern University has officially announced that both FEU Manila and Makati campuses will shift to synchronous classes on September 17, 2025, due to the 3-day transport strike by Manibela.

Students are encouraged to coordinate with their instructors for guidance on class activities for the day. The university is also encouraging students to check Canvas for the official FEU Protocol on Learning Modalities during the suspension of on-campus classes.

Further, take note that university offices, including the Main Library, Shared Hybrid Learning Spaces, and The Huddle, will remain open for onsite transactions and student use.

Stay updated through our TamAnunsyo. 

Source: Far Eastern University

message.text:
#TamAnunsyo | As of today, September 16, 2025, the Far Eastern University has officially announced that both FEU Manila and Makati campuses will shift to synchronous classes on September 17, 2025, due to the 3-day transport strike by Manibela.

Students are encouraged to coordinate with their instructors for guidance on class activities for the day. The university is also encouraging students to check Canvas for the official FEU Protocol on Learning Modalities during the suspension of on-campus classes.

Further, take note that university offices, including the Main Library, Shared Hybrid Learning Spaces, and The Huddle, will remain open for onsite transactions and student use.

Stay updated through our TamAnunsyo. 

Source: Far Eastern University 

#TamaRiseTogether 
#FEUCSO90
